description:
`\{` correctly produces a literal `{` to prevent interpolation, but `\}` does NOT produce a literal `}` - it produces the literal two characters `\}`.

**Repro:**
```
print("\{ and \}")
// Expected: { and }
// Actual:   { and \}
```

Minor inconsistency but surprising when users discover it.

**Test files:** `bugs/strings/str_escape_brace_closing.rad`
